From: Opsero <noreply@opsero.com>
Date: Thu, 15 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm: xlnx: drv: drop manual drm_mode_config_cleanup() in
 xlnx_unbind

xlnx_unbind() calls drm_mode_config_cleanup(drm) followed by
drm_dev_put(drm). In the legacy (non-managed) DRM init style this is
correct, but when any sub-component (e.g. xlnx_mix_connector_init in
connect_drm_bridge=1 mode) creates DRM objects via drm_managed-based
helpers like drm_bridge_connector_init(), those objects register their
own cleanup actions with drm_managed.

The manual drm_mode_config_cleanup() runs first and cleans up the
drm-managed connector (drm_connector_cleanup releases the ida ID, frees
mode state, etc.). Then drm_dev_put() triggers drm_managed_release()
which runs the connector's registered cleanup action a SECOND time:

    WARNING: ida_free called for id=0 which is not allocated.
    Unable to handle kernel NULL pointer dereference at virtual address 0
    pc : 0x0
    lr : drm_connector_free
    Call trace:
      drm_mode_object_put
      __drm_atomic_helper_connector_destroy_state
      drm_atomic_helper_connector_destroy_state
      drm_connector_cleanup
      drm_connector_cleanup_action
      drm_managed_release
      drm_dev_put

Symptom: kernel oops during `poweroff` / `reboot` once the v_mix DRM
bridge pipeline is in use.

Drop the manual drm_mode_config_cleanup() call. drm_dev_put() ->
drm_dev_release() -> drm_managed_release() will run the registered
cleanup actions for any drm-managed objects. Objects allocated via the
legacy non-managed APIs will still be reaped when drm_dev_release frees
the drm_device itself — a small memory leak on shutdown, acceptable
versus the current oops, and only relevant for drivers that still use
legacy alloc paths on top of this xlnx-drm master.

Signed-off-by: Opsero <noreply@opsero.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_drv.c | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_drv.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_drv.c
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_drv.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xlnx/xlnx_drv.c
@@ -291,7 +291,6 @@ static void xlnx_unbind(struct device *dev)
 	}
 	xlnx_crtc_helper_fini(drm, xlnx_drm->crtc);
 	drm_kms_helper_poll_fini(drm);
-	drm_mode_config_cleanup(drm);
 	drm_dev_put(drm);
 }

--
